15/04/2010
ATHENS, Greece -- A homemade bomb exploded late on Wednesday (April 14th) outside the office of ruling PASOK lawmaker Christos Protopapas in Athens.
The blast and ensuing fire caused damage but no injuries.
Earlier in the day, there were four blasts in Thessaloniki.
Three targeted the offices of lawmakers from various political parties.
The fourth occurred near the office of maritime shipping company SAOS, whose owner is involved in a corruption scandal.
All four explosions caused damage but there's been no claim of responsibility yet.
(News In, AFP - 14/04/10)
